div.p:
Schooner James Hamilton Lewis, San Francisco, Cal., U. S.
                    A., left March 7, 1891, San Francisco, on a hunting and fishing voyage;
                    Alexander McLean, master.

March 7.—Calm weather, weighed anchor, and towed to sea;
8 p.m., light W. wind; midnight, light W. wind; latter part, light W. wind;
Farallone light-house, bearing NNW., distant 8 miles.

March 23.—Begins with strong W. wind; midnight, calm;
latter part, light SE. wind; came to anchor in port San Jum; took in supply of
fresh water.

March 24.—Begins with light E. wind; weighed anchor and
made sail; called at Neah Bay for mail; remained one hour and left for sea;
midnight, strong SE. gale. Lat., off Barcley Sound.

April 14.—Begins with lights, wind; midnight, calm;
latter part, light E. wind; came to anchor in Port Sawjun, and took in fresh
water; sent a boat ashore to Neah Bay for mail.

June 26.—Begins with strong SE. wind and fog; midnight,
strong SE. wind and fog; latter part, strong SE. wind and fog. Lat. 55° N.;
long. 157° W.

June 27.—Begins with strong SE. wind; midnight, more
moderate; latter part, light SW. wind; came to anchor at Sand Point, Alaska;
took in fresh water.

July 14.—Begins with strong NE. wind and fog at times;
latter part, strong NE. wind and fog at times. Lat. 50° 45′ N.; long 169° 20′
E.

July 17.—Begins with light SE. wind and rain at times;
latter part, light SE. wind and rain at times. Lat. 51° 30′ N.; long. 175° 10′
E.

July 19.—Begins with light E. wind and fog at times;
latter part, light E. wind and fog at times. Lat. 51° 40′ N.; long. 179° 20′
E.

July 21.—Begins with strong S. wind and fog at times;
latter part, strong S. wind and fog at times. Lat. 50° 50′ N.; long. 177° 25′
E.
